The article discusses President Obama's budget proposal to advance Mission Innovation, a global commitment to accelerate clean energy innovation. In November, 20 countries pledged to double their governments' investments in clean energy R&D over five years. The Breakthrough Energy Coalition, spearheaded by Bill Gates, also aims to bridge the funding gap for innovative technologies. The goal is to limit the rise in global temperatures and increase access to clean and affordable energy. President Obama announced a proposal to double federal investment in clean energy research and development from $6.4 billion in FY 2016 to $12.8 billion in FY 2021. The investment portfolio includes various agencies such as the Department of Energy, National Science Foundation, National Aeronautics and Space Administration, and more. These investments will support research, development, and demonstration activities across a range of clean energy technologies.